      <div xml:id="NA146-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piṉṉiṉṟa talaivaṉ muṉṉilaip puṟamoḻiyākat tōḻi kēṭpac colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what [HE] said so that the confidante would hear, while there was slander against him who was standing behind [her].</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA146">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            villāp pūviṉ kaṇṇi cūṭi</l>
<l>            nallē muṟuvaleṉap pallūr tiritaru</l>
<l>            neṭumāp peṇṇai maṭaṉmā ṉōyē</l>
<l>            kaṭaṉaṟi maṉṉar kuṭainiḻaṟ pōlap</l>
<l>            peruntaṇ ṇeṉṟa maraniḻaṟ ciṟitaḻin </l>
<l>            tiruntaṉai ceṉmō vaḻaṅkuka cuṭareṉa</l>
<l>            varuḷik kūṭu mārva mākka</l>
<l>            ṇallē meṉṉuṅ kiḷavi vallō</l>
<l>            ṉeḻuti yaṉṉa kāṇṭaku vaṉappi</l>
<l>            ṉaiyaṇ māyō ḷaṇaṅkiya </l>
<l>            maiya ṉeñca meṉmoḻik koḷiṉē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O you on the palmyra horse,</l>
<l rend="indent">turning about in many villages, saying “I have great confusion”,</l>
<l rend="indent2">wearing a chaplet of flowers that are not sold,</l>
<l>go, you that have been,</l>
<l rend="indent">slightly desolate, in the shade of the tree that brings great coolness,</l>
<l rend="indent3">as the parasol of a king knowing [his] duty,</l>
<l>– if you take my word, [you with] an infatuated heart</l>
<l rend="indent">tormented by the dark one, the beautiful one,</l>
<l rend="indent2">of a beauty fit to be seen, as if drawn by a capable [painter],</l>
<l>the word<note place="foot">Does <term xml:lang="ta">kiḷavi</term> take up <term xml:lang="ta">eṉ moḻi</term>? If not, how to construe?</note> that says: "we are good people,</l>
<l rend="indent">with affection that is worthy(?) [and] considerate,</l>
<l rend="indent">saying ‘may the [sun's] glow wander'<note place="foot">I.e. "may the sun go down before you move on".</note></l>
        </lg>
         </div>
